==English==
====Etymology====
From {{Arab.}} الدبران  (al-dabarān), meaning "the follower" (of the [[Pleiades]])

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Aldebaran'''
#{{astronomy}}: A [[binary star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Taurus]], an [[orange]] [[giant]], 68 [[light-year]]s from [[Earth]], and one of the [[brightest]] stars in the [[sky]].